      "source": "https://thesunshinerepublic.com/2025/12/30/royal-palm-beach-florida-a-village-built-around-the-trees/"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "The village’s origins trace back to a 1950s purchase of 65,000 acres by Food Fair magnates, turning a Seminole hunting ground into a planned community.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        16
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Royal_Palm_Beach%2C_Florida"
    },
    {
      "id": 5,
      "text": "Arthur Desser’s 1960s vision sparked the initial development, but bankruptcy in 1961 led Friedland to take over and continue the project.",
